# Cursor Rules — apps/wedding-website

## Context
Indian wedding website. React 18 + TypeScript strict + Vite SWC + Tailwind v3 + Framer Motion v11.
Bilingual: English (dev default) and Hindi (prod default) via react-i18next.
Fixed theme: saffron + maroon + gold + ivory. Ganesh & Lakshmi divine motif.

## Imports
- Shared components: `import { Button } from '@shared/ui'`
- Shared hooks: `import { useCountdown } from '@shared/hooks'`
- Shared utils: `import { cn, fadeInUp } from '@shared/utils'`
- App internals: `import { WeddingConfig } from '@app/config/types'`

## i18n
- Every user-facing string must use `const { t } = useTranslation('namespace')`
- Never hardcode English or Hindi text in JSX
- Add new keys to BOTH `src/i18n/locales/en/` and `src/i18n/locales/hi/` simultaneously
- Namespace per section: common, home, story, ceremonies, schedule, gallery, party, travel, rsvp, faq

## Component Structure
- Layout components in `src/components/layout/`
- Home page sections in `src/components/sections/`
- Ceremony detail pages in `src/components/ceremonies/`
- Page-level components in `src/pages/`
- Router config in `src/router/index.tsx`

## Animation Rules
- All Framer Motion variants from `@shared/utils` — never define inline variants
- Use `AnimatedSection` from `@shared/ui` for scroll reveals
- Ceremony pages use `pageTransition` variant from `@shared/utils`

## Theme
- Colors: saffron, maroon, gold, ivory, marigold, divine (from tailwind.config.ts)
- Fonts: font-display (Playfair), font-body (Poppins), font-hindi (Noto Devanagari), font-script (Dancing Script)
- Never use raw hex colors — always Tailwind tokens

## Config
- All personal wedding details in `src/config/wedding.config.ts`
- Types for config in `src/config/types.ts`
- Never hardcode bride/groom names, dates, venues in components
